  "repo_truth": "Fresh read-only review of the exact 27-entry HCM-2.2 four-times-remediated planning subject. Review 4 required remediation of registry identity/durability, initial quorum, CTAP2.1 registration/assertion closure, timestamp identity, promotion recovery ownership, and standalone lifecycle durability. The subject remains planning-only; independently reproduce every exact contract and inherit no clean conclusion.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Remain read-only and replay the sorted 27-entry manifest and aggregate fingerprint before review.",
    "Review every subject byte: 00, 04, 06, four immutable prior dispatches, SPEC, all exact contract/schema/vector/JCS fixtures, plan, unchecked todo, planning proof, and four remediation records.",
    "Read unchanged 01, 02, 03, 05, 07, 08, HCM-0.6 decision, selected HCM-2.1 record/packet/proof, exact live definition assets, and engine/compiler/flow/CLI/skill/template/test sources only as needed.",
    "Run bounded read-only manifest, Markdown/link, Git, handoff/schema, exact schema/JCS/fingerprint, profile/intake, CTAP2.1 registration/assertion, immutable registry, runtime-record identity, promotion/lifecycle durability, byte-contract, cross-platform, determinism, security, bridge, and classification checks.",
    "Return findings first with exact file/line evidence through the built-in channel."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
    "No edits, staging, commits, new dispatches, global handoffs, ledger writes, or user task hops.",
    "No Rust, Cargo, production definitions, runtime fixtures/tests/product/generated-skill/pipeline, HCM-2.3+, Phase-3, SDK, Tauri, Substrate, contract, dock, or publication implementation.",
    "Do not invent alternate schema/intake bytes, fingerprint/ref behavior, approval/identity/registry trust, transaction visibility, lifecycle, renderer, migration, compatibility mode, bridge, or sibling-family scope.",
    "Do not treat prior findings/remediation, passing reproduction, or contingent planning status as proof that the twenty-seven-entry subject is clean."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Invoke required skills in order, remain read-only, replay the exact 27-entry manifest/aggregate, and return BLOCKED if any byte differs.",
    "Review findings first in Critical, Required, Optional, Nit order with exact file/line, violated authority, failure, smallest remediation, and missing or invalidated proof.",
    "Reproduce all six exact schema documents/entries, eleven literal JCS lines/vectors, twelve runtime-record fingerprint/ID vectors, complete profile source lists, dependency graph, fingerprints, old-byte preservation, exact-ref acyclicity, and independent-encoder contract.",
    "Verify the full literal sixteen-row intake, schema/retained-field validation value, every leaf source, value-versus-quality-waiver rule, all-mode equivalence, and candidate basis.",
    "Verify the fixed non-empty initial-Charter quorum; acyclic immutable registry state/transition graph; committed registry mutation journal/recovery; native CTAP2.1 MakeCredential/GetAssertion, RP/clientDataHash/signed-preimage/UP/UV/counter contract; exact pair coverage; honest assurance claim; and native refusal.",
    "Verify ownership-free promotion recovery never deletes final content-addressed records; total crash-state recovery; authority visibility; basis equality; reader locking; standalone lifecycle-event journal/recovery/replay; fixed lock order; and promotion clearance atomicity.",
    "Verify canonical/Markdown byte grammars/fixtures, C03/C04, product cutover, bridges, proof wall, deletion gates, CRITICAL impact warning, planning-only status, primary commit, and separate parent closeout.",
    "Return CLEAN only if no valid Critical or Required finding remains; otherwise CHANGES_REQUIRED or BLOCKED. Make no edits."
  ],
